The paper proposes a new approach to manifold learning using genetic programming, which is a machine learning technique. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of interpretable trees, which suggests a focus on explainable AI, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of manifold learning in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses future directions of research, which suggests a focus on software development (cs.SD).
